#        (typed separate typed `lnd` typed instances typed
#        per typed currency)
#     2. Operator typed runs typed `connext` typed L2 client
#        for typed ETH + typed ERC-20 typed token trades
#     3. Operator typed runs typed `xud` — which typed
#        connects to typed each typed `lnd` instance via typed
#        gRPC (using typed `--lnd.[currency].host` +
#        `--lnd.[currency].port` + typed macaroon auth) + typed
#        connects to typed `connext` typed client (using typed
#        `--connext.host` + `--connext.port`)
#     4. xud typed joins the typed XU peer-to-peer typed
#        order-book gossip network on typed `--p2p.port`
#        (optionally typed routed through typed Tor via typed
#        `--p2p.tor` + `--p2p.torport`)
#     5. xud typed maintains a typed local typed orderbook of
#        typed buy/sell typed orders + typed matches incoming
#        peer orders typed against typed local orders
#     6. typed Matched orders typed trigger typed Atomic Swap
#        execution: typed sending side typed creates typed
#        HTLC on typed source chain, typed receiving side
#        typed claims via typed preimage reveal, typed atomic
#        property typed guaranteed by typed shared typed hash
#        + typed deadlock-free typed timelock
#     7. Operator typed interacts via typed `xucli` typed
#        gRPC commands (covered separately as `_xucli`):
#        typed `xucli buy`, typed `xucli sell`, typed `xucli
#        listorders`, typed `xucli getinfo`, typed `xucli
#        balance`, etc.
